<br />
<br />That depends on what you mean by bottleneck. The 65816 certainly is a barrier as you don't have a whole lot of CPU time. I'm not certain about the CPU&lt;-&gt;PPU interface (I assume you mean speed of DMA) is a huge issue. I mean everyone would love even faster DMA so you could update even more tiles and background data each frame. 
<br />
<br />Both <span class="posthilit">SNES</span> and Genesis despite their issues were able to produce amazing top quality games. There was a big thread about this sort of thing on Spritesmind forums, basically a Sega forum similar to Nesdev.</div>

